<refnamediv><refname>imcalchist</refname><refpurpose>Compute per-channel image histograms.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>[counts, cells] = imcalchist(im, bins)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>im</term><listitem><para>Input grayscale or multichannel image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>bins</term><listitem><para>Optional number of histogram bins. When omitted, the default <function>imhist</function> binning is used.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>counts</term><listitem><para>Histogram counts. Multichannel images return one column per channel.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>cells</term><listitem><para>Histogram bin center values.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imcalchist</function> extends <function>imhist</function> to return one histogram per channel.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
im = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/" + "baboon.png"));
[counts, cells] = imcalchist(im, 16);
plot(cells,counts(:,1),'r');
plot(cells,counts(:,2),'g');
plot(cells,counts(:,3),'b');
]]></programlisting></refsection>
